4 TEXT Photo Name: MARY ELIZABETH WILSON* (1862 - 1947): Burial: Knights of Pythias Cemetery, Frankton, Madison County, Indiana, USA Description: Birth: Mar., 1862 Death: May 7, 1947 Anderson Daily Bulletin: 6 Oct 1947 MARY E. BROWN EXPIRES SUNDAY Mrs. Ma
5 CONC ry E. Brown, age 85, Florida Station, widow of Samuel Brown died yesterday morning at 1 o&apos;clock at her home. Funeral services will be conducted tomarrow afternoon at 2 o&apos;clock at the Florida Methodist Church with Rev. Ralph McCory, pasto
5 CONC r of the Frankfort Holiness Church, in charge. Burial will be in the K.P.I.O.O.F cemetery at Frankton. The body was removed from the Nuckols Funeral Home to the family residence this afternoon and will be taken to the church tomarrow afteroon a
5 CONC t 1 o&apos;clock to lie in state until the hour of the service. Mrs. Brown was born and reared in Pulaski county, near Rochester, daughter of Isaac and Martha Wilson. She moved to Madison county when she was twenty years old. Her husband preceded i
5 CONC n death in 1936. Mrs. Brown was a member of the Ironwood Christian Church and the Bethany Brotherhood and Sisterhood. Surviving are six daughters, Mrs. Charles Yattaw and Mrs Myrtle Hawkins, both of Anderson, Mrs. Fred Beeman, Frankton and Mrs. Wil
5 CONC lis Ashby, Mrs. Blanch Ashby and Mrs. Marie Kimmerling, all of Florida Station; four sons, Willard Brown of Anderson, George V. Brown, Miami, Fla; and Earl and Charles Brown, both of Frankton; three sisters, Mrs. Jack Closser, Frankton, Mrs. Anna W
5 CONC ashburn and Mrs. Clara Ashby, both of Florida Station; one brother, Ora Wilson, Miami, Fla; 17 grandchildren, 33 great-grandchildren and one great great grandchild. ** (photos from &quot;Watkins Family Tree&quot; by CSWatkins) Family links: Spouse
5 CONC : Samuel Daniel Brown (1857 - 1936) Children: Earl Jacob Brown (1903 - 1970)* *Calculated relationship Burial: Knights of Pythias Cemetery Frankton Madison County Indiana, USA Edit Virtual Cemetery info [?] Created by: Sharon Benefiel Palmer Recor
