2 CONC ison county. Funeral arrangements have not been completed. He is survived by a widow, Mary; four sons, George and Willard at home; Earl, near Frankton; charles near Lapel; six daughters, Mrs. Marie Kimmerling near Frankton; Mrs. Charles Yettaw, Mrs
2 CONC . Fred Beeman and Mrs. John Hawkins, all near Anderson; Mrs. Willis Ashby and Mrs. Blanch Ashby, of near Florida; four sisters and several grandchildren.  
