1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;span&gt;February 27, 2012&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;a rel="bookmark" href="http://heraldbulletin.com/obituaries/x2054917175/Billy-A-Yattaw" class="url entry-title"&gt;Billy A. Yattaw&lt;/a&gt;  July 4, 1931 - Feb. 26, 201
2 CONC 2 &lt;p&gt;  &lt;span&gt;       &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;                 &lt;/span&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;  DALEVILLE, Ind. &amp;mdash;  	Billy A. Yattaw, 80, of Daleville, died at his residence on Feb. 26, 2012, following a six-year battle with A.L.S.&l
2 CONC t;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	Billy was born July 4, 1931, in Anderson to Charles L. and Gertie Mae  (Brown) Yattaw. He graduated from Anderson High School in 1949.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	He served in the U.S. Army from 1954 to 1956.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	He wo
2 CONC rked at Delco Remy from 1950 until 1984.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	He enjoyed golf and wintering in Silver Springs, Fla. He was a member of the Daleville Masonic Lodge&amp;nbsp; 730.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	He is survived by his children, Tracy (Joseph) Br
2 CONC andon of Anderson;  Teresa Jo Yattaw, Stephen (Kathy) Yattaw, all of Daleville;  grandchildren, Megan (David) Smart of Anderson; Kurtis Yattaw and Kyle  Yattaw, both of Yorktown; sister-in-law, Wanda Yattaw of Huntsville;  brother-in-law, Bill (Car
2 CONC olyn) Hall and sister-in-law Charlotte (Bill)  Huntzinger, all of Anderson; several nieces and nephews and care givers:  Veronica Brummet; Laura Myers, Renee Johnson, Thelma Orick and Merricke  Bennett.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	He was preceded in deat
2 CONC h by his parents; his wife of 54 years Myrna  (Hall) Yattaw, who died Sept. 11, 2011; his in-laws: Robert and Irene  Schlegel, brothers Harold, Glen, Bob and Jack and sisters Mable, Thelma,  Mary, Kate, Jean and Helen.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	Memoria
2 CONC l services will be 1 p.m. Wednesday at Rozelle-Johnson Funeral Service with Chris Mishler officiating.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	Friends may call from 11:00 a.m. until the service.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	Memorial contributions may be given to ALS.</line><
2 CONC /content></metadataxml>
