1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="caret-color: #36322d; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%
2 CONC ; background-color: #fafafa;"&gt;Kathryn "June" Watkins, 93, of Anderson, passed away Sept. 14, 2019, at Northwestern Memorial Hospital, Chicago, Illinois. She was born June 10, 1926, in Anderson, where she resided all of her life.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/sp
2 CONC an&gt;&lt;br style="box-sizing: border-box; caret-color: #36322d; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"&gt;&lt;
2 CONC span style="caret-color: #36322d; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; background-color: #fafafa;"&gt;June wa
2 CONC s a homemaker and mother to four ornery kids and numerous pets. She loved gardening, animals, entertaining, shopping, playing cards, traveling, and spending time with her friends and family.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style="box-sizing: border-bo
2 CONC x; caret-color: #36322d; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;"&gt;&lt;span style="caret-color: #36322d; color
2 CONC : #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; background-color: #fafafa;"&gt;June is survived by her daughters, Karen Miller
2 CONC , Connie (David Heinke) Watkins; grandchildren, Amy Watkins, Gretchen Smith, April Myers, Matthew Watkins, Gustavo Baca-Spittal; six great-grandchildren; and one great-great-grandchild. She was preceded in death by her husband, William V. Watkins
2 CONC ; daughter, Kathy Vaughn; son, John Watkins; her parents, John and Myrtle Hawkins; and her sister, Gretchen Hawkins. The family wished to express their gratitude to June's many caregivers, especially to Becky Williams. Visitation was held Wednesday
2 CONC , Sept. 18, 2019, from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. at Loose Funeral Homes &amp;amp; Crematory, 200 W. 53rd St., Anderson. Services were at 1 p.m. Wednesday, Sept. 18, 2019, at the funeral home. Burial took place in Anderson Memorial Park. In lieu of flowers
2 CONC , memorial contributions could be made to The Arthritis Foundation. www.loosecares.com.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
