2 TITL Jacob M. Webb
1 _OID 6549f173-ad15-45d6-9e6a-61644684391f
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;Jacob Mulford Webb was born on July 7, 1810 in Greene County, Ohio to Cuthbert and Mary (Jarrell) Webb. He married (1) on April 21, 1831 in Greene County, Ohio to Mary Fallis, daughter of Isaac and Mary (Mercy
2 CONC ) Vaughan. She died on July 31, 1876 in Madison County, Indiana, aged 63. He married (2) about 1877 to Rebecca Todd, born April 26, 1819, died August 29, 1897. From the birthplaces of his children in the 1850 census of Jackson Township, Madison Cou
2 CONC nty, Indiana, his child Silas was born in Indiana about 1832, Marenus and Delila were born in Ohio, 1834-37, then the rest of his children were born in Indiana after 1840. Apparently Jacob came to Indiana a brief time before returning to Ohio, the
2 CONC n coming back to Indiana one final time. Jacob M. Webb died on October 12, 1910 in Madison County, Indiana. He and both of his wives are buried in the Prewett Cemetery, Madison County. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;From Deanna Spingola&lt;br&gt;deanna@@spingo
2 CONC la.com&lt;br&gt;His obituary says that he was the youngest of 12 children, and was born three miles from Dayton, Ohio. All of his 6 brothers and 5 sisters preceeded him in death. He was married twice, living over forty years with his first wife, th
2 CONC e mother of his 11 children, 5 boys and 6 girls, eight of which survive. (1908). He lived with his second wife over twenty years. He was on the 1842 tax list for Jackson Co. Another obit says that he was related to most of the Webb&amp;#39;s in Mad
2 CONC ison Co., Indiana. Four sons survived him, all living in Madison Co, Indiana.&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
