1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;font face="times new roman,times" size="3"&gt;His will leaves his homestead of 32 acres to his wife, Martha Ann.&amp;nbsp; These 32 acres lie east of the homestead bounded with Lawrence&amp;#39;s line.&amp;nbsp; Afte
2 CONC r her death the land was given to two daughters, Kate C. Craig and Sarah Riddle.&amp;nbsp; The remainder of the homestead tract supposed to be 48 acres was given to his 3 granddaughters, Jo Ann Craig, Margaret Parker and Kate C.&amp;nbsp; His 3 son
2 CONC s, John Evans, Alfred Gillis and M.F., Craig had the liberty of taking possession of these 48 acres by paying Jo Ann Craig $40 and $20 to each Kate C. and Margaret Parker.&amp;nbsp; He gave his 3 sons half of &amp;quot;the David Carson tract of lan
2 CONC d purchased from Carson heirs by me and John Evans.&amp;quot;&lt;/font&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
