1 _OID a8c54801-ebe0-4195-9601-4031a3574e02
1 DATE 2005
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;William V. Watkins&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; 	&lt;font face="Verdana"&gt;June 16, 1923 - Sept. 11, 2005&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;William Victor ?Bill? Watkin
2 CONC s, 82, Anderson, died Sept. 11, 2005, at St. John?s Medical Center after a sudden illness.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;He  was born June 16, 1923, in Anderson, and was a lifelong Anderson  resident. He retired from Delco Remy in 1982. He was a 1941 graduat
2 CONC e of  Anderson High School.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;He served his country in the U.S. Army  during World War II. He attended the Army specialized training program  at the University of Wyoming and later transferred to the European  Operation where he wa
2 CONC s wounded in action in 1944 and received the Purple  Heart.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;He was a member of Mount Moriah Masonic Lodge for more  than 50 years, Scottish Rite, Valley of Indianapolis and the Murat  Temple Shrine. He was also a teacher in the a
2 CONC dult vocational school and  was the past president of the Industrial Management Club.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;He is  survived by his wife, June (Hawkins) Watkins, whom he married Sept. 16,  1945; four children, Kathy Vaughn, John (Lynn Frazier) Watkin
2 CONC s and Karen  (Barry) Miller, all of Anderson, and Connie (David Heinke) Watkins of  Elmhurst, Ill.; a brother, George Robert (Ruth) Watkins of Muncie; a  sister, Patricia Ritchison of Alexandria; four grandchildren, Amy (Chad)  Edmonson, Gretchen (
2 CONC Cory) Smith, April Myers and Matthew Watkins; five  great-grandchildren; one niece; two nephews; and many loving friends.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;He was preceded in death by his parents, Merle Victor and Clara (Benton) Watkins.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Servic
2 CONC es  will be conducted at 10 a.m. Wednesday at Robert D. Loose Funeral Homes  &amp;amp; Crematory, South Chapel, 200 W. 53rd St., Anderson. Burial will  be in Anderson Memorial Park Cemetery.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Visitation will be 4 to 8 p.m. today a
2 CONC t the South Chapel. Masonic memorial services will be at 7 p.m. by Mount Moriah Lodge.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
