1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Birth:&amp;nbsp; 27 Apr 1951&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;De
2 CONC ath:&amp;nbsp; 21 Jun 2011, Knoxville, Knox County, Tennessee, USA &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Leah Joyce Friend age 60 of Jacksboro Passed away Tuesda
2 CONC y June 21, 2011 at The Ft. Sanders Regional Medical Center in Knoxville.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Leah enjoyed Bible study class, cooking, and reading
2 CONC .&amp;nbsp; She loved spending time with her grandsons and her family. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;She was proceeded in death by her parents Palmer Bark
2 CONC er and Ruby Playforth Barker. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;She is survived by husband Don Friend of Jacksboro, sons Craig Friend and wife Christy of Murf
2 CONC reesboro TN, David Friend of Chattanooga, TN,&amp;nbsp; her brother Trevis Barker of Middletown, OH, her sister: Claudia Taylor Fairfield, OH, and Kimberly Howell Denver Co.&amp;nbsp; Grandchildren: Lancie and Ryan Friend.&amp;nbsp; Several Nieces
2 CONC , Nephews and friends. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Burial will be in Campbell Memorial Garden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial
2 CONC ,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
